OL,3,CThousands of Muslims mark Eid al-Adh
OL,4,Cat The Mubarak Mosque in Farnham
OL,6,FThousands of Muslims have been
OL,7,Fcelebrating one of the most important
OL,8,Fevents in the religion's calendar, at
OL,9,Fa mosque near Farnham in Surrey.
OL,11,FEid al-Adha, also known as the Feast
OL,12,Fof Sacrifice, has been marked at The
OL,13,FMubarak Mosque by families who've come
OL,14,Ftogether for prayer and celebration.
OL,16,FThe event commemorates the willingness
OL,17,Fof Prophet Abraham to sacrifice his
OL,18,Fson, the Prophet Ishmael, in the name
OL,19,Fof god.
