OL,3,CThousands of Muslims mark Eid al-Adh
OL,4,Cat The Mubarak Mosque in Farnham
OL,6,FChildren take a day off school and
OL,7,Fmany adults take a day off work on the
OL,8,Fsecond of two Eid celebrations in
OL,9,FIslam.
OL,11,FOne follows Ramadan, the month of
OL,12,Ffasting, while the one being
OL,13,Fcelebrated today follows the
OL,14,Fcompletion of Hajj, a pilgrimage to
OL,15,FMecca.
OL,17,FAn animal is sacrificed with a third
OL,18,Fgoing to the less fortunate, another
OL,19,Fthird goes to the individual's friends
OL,20,Fand family while the remaining third
OL,21,Fcan then be consumed by themselves.
