OL,3,CThousands of Muslims mark Eid al-Adh
OL,4,Cat The Mubarak Mosque in Farnham
OL,6,FThe occasion also sees an additional
OL,7,Fopportunity for prayer, on top of the
OL,8,Ffive that Muslims would normally
OL,9,Fpractice.
OL,11,FWomen and children have been given
OL,12,Fdedicated an area so they can pray and
OL,13,Flisten to the sermon being delivered,
OL,14,Fwith 3,000 spaces made available.
OL,16,FDr Qurratul-ain Rehman, President of
OL,17,Fthe Ahmadiyya Muslim Women
OL,18,FAssociation, explains why the day is
OL,19,Fso important,
